<br>
At the peak of damage output a fully enabled (59th has all spells) cleric will hit 97dps...  This occurs 13.5 seconds from the start of the first cast.  The mage hits a peek of 86dps at shortly after that at the 16.3 second mark.  The mage will exceed the clerics damage right around 30 seconds.  <br>
<br>
Based on this it could be argued that if your fights are less than 30 seconds the cleric is superior for damage.  The mage will still win for mana efficiency, which leads to a larger overall larger damage total, and theoretically less down time.  I can see where there is the potential for it to be a toss up between these two classes at 59+, under certain conditions.  Under 59 the choice is clear, pick the Mage.<br>
